-- Barclays Hires Brian Wiele as Head of Securitization Syndicate in Americas
-- Tim Catts
-- 2010-07-06T15:30:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/barclays-hires-brian-wiele-as-head-of-securitization-syndicate-in-americas.html

          
          
             Barclays Plc hired  Brian Wiele  of
StormHarbour Securities LP as head of securitization syndicate
in the Americas, according to a memo to the staff.  
 Wiele, 41, started at  Barclays  today as a managing
director, according to spokesman  Brandon Ashcraft , who confirmed
the contents of the memo.  
 Prior to  StormHarbour , Wiele worked for nine years at
Deutsche Bank AG and for 10 years at Credit Suisse Group AG, and
was head of U.S. asset-backed syndicate at both companies,
according to the memo.  
 At Barclays, Wiele will report to  Mark Bamford , head of
global fixed-income syndicate.  
